caption: Got there about one, it wasn't busy. There was fast and courteous service. The place has a great feel to it.
Certainly a spot worth trying, the food is good and well prepared, the rates are convenient and it is constantly neat here. Keep up the good work.

I meet friends in this nice place from time to time! This is the best place to eat.  I visit this place at least once a month. The cooking is fantastic, the staff is polite and the prices are reasonable. I like meeting in this restaurant for a nice dinner.

Delicious dark roast coffee with a range of organic sweeteners available and organic milk/cream. Breakfast sandwiches on fresh baked organic rolls, made to order, and organic apple bread. Lunch combo of soup and salad/sandwich. Everything I have eaten from Hannah's has been very good!
Professional and courteous staff as always.
Rude staff, dirty place, left because I couldn't get somebody to take my order due to acting busy around 2pm. Won't return
overpriced

The price is over $10 for a sandwich that is way to thin to hold all those ingredients.  My sandwich fell apart as I was eating it and made a mess.  I do like the option for chips or almonds, hence why not a 1 star.  Make your buns wider and shorter and does not fall apart instantly.
Just brilliant
Service is great. Food is overpriced
Great veggie bomb sandwich!
High quality sandwiches. I specifically like their breakfast sandwiches
Great coffee and sandwiches
Good was good but portions were a bit small for the price.
Organic, local, good quality, clean, and fast! ❤️
Good, but way over priced.
Healthy and simple sandwiches with good ingredients. They have nice music too.
Bread was great for 5$ with a coffee can’t beat it

Excellent sanwitchs made with excellent ingredients. The wall of chocolate is very good and they have a daily special if you buy a chocolate bar between 2 pm and 4 pm, you receive a coffee or espresso for free.
Yum! Great spot to grab lunch. Healthy comfort food.
Love Hannah's. Food is fresh & tasty
(Translated by Google) Best organic coffee & chocolates  (Original) Best organic coffee & Chocolats
Great food but small volume
(Translated by Google) Good sandwiches and salads, excellent ingredients.  (Original) Buoni panini e insalate, ottimi ingredienti.
Excellent food but it's priced for the quality you get and is therefore not cheap.
Proper German-style Brezeln/Brezn-miles ahead of any of that mushy, floppy rubbish you normally get in America. All fresh ingredients and brilliant flavour combos on sandwiches. Fair pricing.
Perfect lunch date spot with a girl named Erin;)

For the quality of food you are receiving the price is perfect.  No hormones, gms, or pesticides in the food.  Portions are great for someone conscientious of their healthy.  The service was friendly and fast.  Something I look for wherever I go.
(Translated by Google) It is closed for reform and is not reported on this page.  (Original) Está  cerrado por reforma y no se informa en esta página.
This seems like a nice restaurant.

Plenty of unique "fancier" sandwiches options with a bit smaller portions at a bit of a higher price. Both sandwiches look small, but are more filling than they appear. The pretzel buns are amazing and the service is quick. The food is really great in terms of flavor and options, but the portion size and price stop me from coming back more often.
Love this place. The pretzel rolls are delicious and there are so many great options and neat ingredients to pick from.

I had breakfast today here. The place was empty (lazy Saturday in the Loop) so I could spend a couple of minutes more to decide. They have a lot of options for sandwiches. I took the "SPANISH SERRANO HAM + MANCHEGO CHEESE" wecken which was amazing. Therefore I decided try  another wecken: a "SERGIO'S SPECIAL" , very nice but not the same level of the first. There is not much space to eat there but if you're lucky to get a spot they have the New York Times and other Chicago-based magazines. And relaxing music. A nice start of day !
The food is great, but the prices are way too high for the quantity of food you get. The staff is great, though.
Good place for overpriced, overly complex sandwiches but hey, where else can you go in downtown.
Not your average sandwich shop. Nice change of pace with some unique ingredients.
My absolute favorite sandwich shop in the city.
Delicious slightly small for the price sandwiches.

Amazing :) What a great place this is, I will come back soon. Whenever I see anyone from out of town, I always tell them, go to Hannah's Bretzel. You wont regret it. I remember my first time I ate here, I got an amazing sandwich. Not only is the food here spectacular, the customer service is even better!!

The sandwiches and house made chips are definitely good, but both are quite small servings compared to other sandwich joints in the loop.  I had the Sergio Special, and quite enjoyed it, but was left still feeling hungry.  Pret is a bit cheaper and more food for your same fresh organic sandwich.
extremely overpriced for small portions of mediocre food.
(Translated by Google) very good  (Original) muy bueno
Fresh ingredients prepared in front of you. Love their sandwich recipes!

I placed a catering order for breakfast from Hannah's for our corporate meeting. The food arrived without the disposable plates. Coffee came without the cream or milk. The food was okay quality considering the price they charged for it. When they are charging over the top price for their products the least they could do is match their service if they cannot exceed it.

Hannah's has some innovative sandwiches with quality ingredients. The best one I've had by far is the Bavari-Asian. The bretzel is obviously a highlight and my only complaint is that the sandwiches are a little smaller than I would prefer, particularly for the price charged. The house made chips are a nice complement.
Thank you for being gluten free friendly and offering glove changes. I will be back here a lot more because of this.  Thanks for the great sandwich. :)

I ate here for the first time today, I had the Sergio's special. It was good, and had a lot of flavors, and you could tell you were getting your money's worth for the ingredients, but at the same time when I finished the sandwich and the chips.. I was still hungry. So it was healthy and you could tell that for the $10 sandwich, you were getting your value in ingredients, but not in volume.  Ideal for people who care more about what they put in their bodies than I do, but don't care about being full.

I wanted to like this place so much -- I was in the loop for a class on a saturday afternoon with a short break for lunch. It was fine, it was actually pretty ok, if my girlfriend had sent me to work with it packed in my lunch bag though I wouldn't have been compelled to tell her it was great and I wanted it again. Price point makes it difficult to recommend for what it is.

I love this place. The bread is fresh, the food is fabulous! The sides are perfect! There isn't anything I could say to under or over play this place. It's just that good... sure, it's pricey, but you are getting the quality you look for during the lunch hour.

Went here and caught up with my girlfriends. Portions are small for the price. Not my kind of place for a lunch spot. Highly recommend if you have a healthy eating lifestyle as everything is organic and gourmet. Spent $20 on lunch on myself alone and still left hungry.

Usually have their serrano ham and manchego cheese sandwhich, which is my go to sandwhich at Hanna's. I consider it a treat, as I find it is expensive for the portion size, which is just right on light days, but not good enough on hungry days. Great selection of international chocolate.
This is the go-to place for my coworkers for lunch.  It's a little expensive for what you get but it's consistently good and much better than other sandwich options for lunch.
I am in love! The sandwiches taste amazing. You can really feel the love and care in each sandwich. The use of a pretzel as bread makes it even better. Every deli should use these green techniques.

Came here a few years ago for lunch and loved the fresh ingredients and especially the pretezel roll (yes wendy's is copying off of this now). Also recently went here for breakfast and the egg sandwiches are phenominal. Eggs with vegetables and cheese cooked up fresh before your eyes on a toasted whole grain pretzel bun.... yum! They also have coffee/tea/soda and an assortment of german chocolate.  Go early for lunch as the line can get long. Don't think there is seating indoors, but there are a few tables outside which has a nice little biergarten feel. Definitely my favorite lunch spot (second to Chipotle) in the North West Loop.

We ordered about 15 sandwhiched for a lunch time meeting. They have a large selection of delicious sandwhiched which include some vegan options. The boxed lunches included chips, a sandwhich, a fruit cup and a piece of chocolate. I would totally recommend it. Everyone enjoyed their lunch.
The most delicious sandwich I've had!! Love the environmental friendly atmosphere
Delicious and healthy sandwiches! Best quick lunch spot in Chicago.
Best place in the city for a quick lunch

Great local organic food stuffs. I've tried several things on the menu and only one thing was not delicious. Slightly pricey but definitely worth it. Lots of vegan and vegetarian choices. I'd suggest the apple and brie.
Amazing food! So healthy, so tasty!

great feel,  great food.  You instantly know what this place is about once you walk through the door.  Sandwiches are prepared right in front of you which is nice,  and they provide a nice quantity of different ingredients.  My sandwich had an awesome flavor mix,  with mango, avocado and jalapeño on ham,  and I loved it.  Certainly worth the trip in you're downtown

Hannah's is a tasty sandwich that is different than most. Apples and different types of spreads on the sandwich are very unique and once you try it you won't think it's weird. The sandwich, however, is not very big and quite frankly is a bit too expensive. I'll go to this place once every two months with co-workers, other than that, IMO it is too expensive for what it is.
The best organic sandwiches at this place. I go for Sergio's special, with tomatoes.

Just get in the line and treat yourself to a sandwich of your choice.  My one and only favorite is the Hannah's Club.  Just let the staff know what you want and don't want on your order.  All sammies come with a choice of veggie chips, soy nuts or tamari roasted almonds.  I also like to grab a little bit of any of their gourmet chocolates.

Great sandwich, but not for $10.  I got the turkey + farmhouse cheddar, which came on a relatively smallish baguette; no sides.  When the cashier rung up my order, I gave the "deer in the headlights" look.  $9.86 for a small sandwich?  Really?  The sandwich was very good (not excellent), but at these prices, I'd be surprised if Hannah's stays in business for much longer.  Come on...$10 for a small sandwich, in this economy?  No thanks.
This place is awesome. It has a wide selection of European chocolates, and the sandwiches are unique and delcious. A must try, you won't be disappointed. The pretzel bread is to die for.

Organic breads and upscale ingredients make for very tasty sandwiches! My favorite is the Thanksgiving which is turkey and cranberry sauce. The grass fed sirlon is also great, as is the apple brie on multigrain bread. They have cute lunch boxes with a sandwich, chips, fruit and chocolate which is great for catered meetings.  For larger orders they have platters available and they deliver.
Best sandwich shop downtown. I've been to many & this place takes the cake!
The best organic in the city

Love their pretzel bread, soft pretzels (in salt or sesame seed) and their various vegetarian options. Always a great option in the loop for lunch, just a little pricier than some.  Tip: If you just want a soft pretzel (not the bun), you can always get one whenever you want, as long as they don't run out.

Definitely recommend. Good variety of different sandwiches. There isn't an area to sit down within the restaurant, but being in the Loop you're able to walk to a variety of different places to eat outside when it's nice.
Smaller portions than you may be used to at a normal sandwich shop but the unique and tasty sandwich is absolutely worth it!

Who doesn't love pretzel bread after all what's not to like?  They do a nice job having fresh ingredients prepared by knowledgeable people.  The line gets a little crazy during the week at lunch time but they are usually well prepared and get you through pretty efficiently.  Reasonable prices and good food make this an overall thumbs up for a workday lunch.
Great pretzels.
